{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f466b841-1b83-45fa-ae2f-ccce10969c22","content":"In .NET 10, the iOS-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a **cross-platform** `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page`. You no longer need the iOS platform-specific namespace.\n\n**Before (.NET 9):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**After (.NET 10):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"All\">\n```\n\nThe `SafeAreaRegions` enum values are:\n- `All` — insets content from all safe area edges (status bar, notch, home indicator)\n- `None` — content extends edge-to-edge, ignoring safe areas\n\nYou can remove the `xmlns:ios` namespace declaration if it was only used for `UseSafeArea`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8cff6772-23e6-4cf6-938a-8beaf9b580c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a known breaking change in .NET MAUI.\n\nIn .NET 10, the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` attached property was removed/deprecated. The replacement is to use the `SafeAreaRegions` property directly on the `Page` (or `ContentPage`).\n\nLet me provide the correct answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI changes:\n\nIn .NET 10, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a cross-platform `Page.SafeAreaRegions` property. \n\nThe new property is cross-platform and doesn't require the iOS-specific namespace, accepting values like `All` (the default that respects all safe areas), `None` (which ignores them), or specific regions depending on your needs. The `SafeAreaRegions` property accepts an enum with values like `All`, `None`, and individual sides, so this cross-platform approach replaces the old iOS-specific namespace and `UseSafeArea` attribute entirely.","outputTokens":893,"requestId":"A853:77FDA:7017E3:81777D:69FBE54A"},"id":"0ab17507-36db-4679-aaae-1a263b826e7b","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:05:32.197Z","parentId":"cfda0295-df12-4664-9d40-b0951543ff21"}
